But the JVM’s coverage report suggests it does execute. I’m wondering if the native image build could select `--initialize-at-build-time` for everything instead?\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "I refined the dedicated active-class test at:\n\n- `tests/src/org.hsqldb/hsqldb/2.4.1/src/test/java/org_hsqldb/hsqldb/DatabaseManagerTest.java`\n\nIt now reaches `org.hsqldb.util.DatabaseManager` through HSQLDB’s public `MainInvoker.invoke(...)` API, which forces `DatabaseManager` class initialization and therefore executes the `<clinit>` path containing the `Class.forName(...)` lookup.\n\nHowever, the remaining dynamic-access report frame is:\n\n```text\norg.hsqldb.util.DatabaseManager.<clinit>(Unknown Source)\n```\n\nBecause the HSQLDB 2.4.1 artifact does not expose line/source debug info for this call site, the dynamic-access coverage reporter cannot associate the executed `<clinit>` bytecode with a JaCoCo-covered source line. So the test reaches the supported behavior, but the report may still be unable to mark this `Unknown Source` call site as covered.\n\nNo metadata or native-image config files were modified.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_06d4152379d908aa016a119b0a11fc819697fb140cdb875386\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 35990, "output": 2699, "cacheRead": 21504, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 60193, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1779538659592, "responseId": "resp_06d4152379d908aa016a119ae51b9881968e744da1a4599fa9"}, "toolResults": []}
